<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 2:49PM MDT  by NWS Pocatello</headline>
<description>...THUNDERSTORMS MOVING NORTHEAST TOWARD OAKLEY RESERVOIR THROUGH
345 PM MDT...
At 247 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southwest of Oakley Reservoir, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain, wind gusts to 35 mph, and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Oakley Reservoir, Oakley and City Of Rocks.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
